<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1624,1940]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis box="[136,324,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">J.R.I. Wood et al</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[339,578,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">24854, 25193, 25841</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[634,704,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">26081</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode box="[720,775,1661,1687]" country="Bolivia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15532" name="Herbario Nacional de Bolivia, Universidad Mayor de San Andr�s" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">LPB</collectionCode>
, K) are apparently the first Bolivian records for this species representing a significant range extension beyond the previously known distribution in central and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1383,1451,1697,1723]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barneby, R. C." box="[144,458,1733,1759]" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 835" part="65" refString="Barneby, R. C. (1991) Sensitivae Censitae: a description of the genus Mimosa L. (Mimosaceae) in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 65: 1 - 835." title="Sensitivae Censitae: a description of the genus Mimosa L. (Mimosaceae) in the New World" type="journal article" year="1991">Barneby 1991: 129 MAP 9</bibRefCitation>
). Collected in three disparate localities in Provs. Angel Sandoval and Chiquitos, 
<collectingRegion country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
, potentially widespread in eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[583,668,1769,1795]" name="Bolivia" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, and apparently becoming more frequent following disturbance along the line of the newly constructed road from 
<collectingRegion box="[635,759,1805,1831]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[797,865,1805,1831]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mamani, F. &amp; Pozo, P. &amp; Soto, D. &amp; Villarroel, D. &amp; Wood, J. R. I." bookContentInfo="199 pp." box="[881,1017,1805,1831]" journalOrPublisher="Museo de Historia Natural ' Noel Kempff Mercado', Santa Cruz" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" refString="Mamani, F., Pozo, P., Soto, D., Villarroel, D. &amp; Wood, J. R. I. (2011) Guia Darwin de las Plantas de los Cerrados de la Chiquitania. Museo de Historia Natural ' Noel Kempff Mercado', Santa Cruz, 199 pp." title="Guia Darwin de las Plantas de los Cerrados de la Chiquitania" type="book" year="2011">Wood 2011</bibRefCitation>
). This material is a good match for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="acutistipula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">M. acutistipula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although 
<emphasis box="[391,583,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">J.R.I. Wood et al</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[599,669,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">25193</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[727,797,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">26081</emphasis>
(both from Quimome) have leaves with fewer (14–19 as opposed to 20–31) pairs of leaflets per pinna than typical material. In 
<collectingCountry box="[925,1007,1877,1903]" name="Bolivia" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
this species occurs locally around rock platforms (known locally as “lajas”) and in similar places on roadsides.
</paragraph>
